						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone in the temple of Kalamēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>Kannara—A.D. 1254.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Ānanda</hi> during the reign of <hi rend="bold">Kaṁdaradēva, Pushya śu. Pūrṇimā, Monday, Makara-Saṁkramaṇa.</hi> The details are irregular. The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1254, December 25.</hi> The week-day, however, was <hi rend="bold">Friday.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">Makara-saṁkramaṇa</hi> occurred on Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It records the death of a hero (name lost) in a fight. <hi rend="italic">Sarvādhikāri</hi> <hi rend="bold">Chavuḍi-seṭṭi</hi> is mentioned. Further on in the record, the date is repeated but what follows is damaged and lost.</p>						

						</summary>
